Sabellaria nanella
was originally described from the Indo-West Pacific, but has also been reported from the eastern Pacific, from Ecuador (
Kirtley 1994
), and along the Atlantic Ocean, from the coast of Ceará (
Kirtley 1994
), Paraíba (Santos et al. 2011 ;
Lomonaco et al. 2011
), Bahia (
Lana & Bremec 1994
), Espírito Santo, Rio de Janeiro (
Rullier & Amoureux 1979
;
Lana & Bremec 1994
), São Paulo, and Uruguay (
Lana & Bremec 1994
).
